[It is interesting how defining an adulterant is different between enterohemorrhagic _E. coli_ in beef and _Salmonella_ in chicken, despite the fact that both are commensals in their zoonotic host, can be killed by cooking, and are pathogenic in humans. In parallel, small turtles are illegal to sell, but small chicks are not, yet both can be vehicles for salmonellosis. - Mod.LL

